<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" CalDefCategory="HMI" Description="Gis-513">
  <CalDefFileVersion>6</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>2/19/15</Date>
    <Description>Fixed Values</Description>
    <Author>Samer Khatib</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>12/1/2015</Date>
    <Description>Within this CalDef file, updated the default values for the Enable_Application_MirrorLink and Default_mirrorlink_notification_setting CALs from True to False since the direction at this point is that Mirror Link will not be implemented.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>6/10/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within GIS513_DeviceProjection.caldef file, maded the following updates: Added  the ENABLE_APPLICATIONBAIDU_CARLIFE calibration for enabling the BAIDU CARLIFE captured as a requred calibration in the GIS-513. Also, updated the description of the following three calibrations (1.) Enable_Application_MirrorLink, 2.) Enable_Application_Apple_Carplay, and 3.) Enable_application_google_Automotive_link) to clarify that these calibrations control enabling/disabling the specfically the specific related features and not the Application on HomeScreen. Separate calibrations within the GIS-501 and GIS501_HomeScreenUI.caldef control enabling/disabling the Application on HomeScreen for these features. Also, updated the usage field for all of the calibrations in this caldef file to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
    <Description>Added GEM usage to all of the calibrations in the GIS513_DeviceProjection.caldef. Since all of these calibrations fell within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="Enables/Disables Baidu CarLife feature" Name="ENABLE_APPLICATIONBAIDU_CARLIFE" References="GIS-513 5.1.1.1* Calibration Items" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_ttOfUE8REeep_Namk9CiEQ</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>6/10/2017</Date>
      <Description>Initial release of this calibration</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="Enables/Disables MirrorLink feature" Name="Enable_Application_MirrorLink" References="GIS-513 5.1.1.1* Calibration Items" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_kSqKAMZZEeOEzdA9o_rOxw</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>12/1/2015</Date>
      <Description>Updated the default value for this CAL from True to False.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>6/10/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the descprition of this calibration to clarify this calibration enables/disables the feature and not the HomeScreen Application. Also, updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>4</Version>
      <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="Enables or disables the MirrorLink Notifications menu item" Name="Enable_mirrorlink_Notification" References="GIS-513 5.1.1.1*MY17 Calibration Items" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_nnTxoMZZEeOEzdA9o_rOxw</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/10/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="The user can toggle MirrorLink Notifications on or off by tapping this list item. The Default is on." Name="Default_mirrorlink_notification_setting" References="GIS-513 5.1.1.1*MY17 Calibration Items" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_q-izMMZZEeOEzdA9o_rOxw</CalID>
